    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-07-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-07-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="483"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d483">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/15232</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Chief of the Division of Far Eastern
                        Affairs</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Hamilton</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-07-13">July 13,
                            1939</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Suma<note n="96" xml:id="d483fn96">Counselor of the Japanese Embassy.</note>
                    said that the Embassy had received a telegram from the Japanese Foreign Office
                    reporting the representations made by Mr. Dooman to the Japanese Foreign
                    Minister on July 10 in regard to the recent bombings of Chungking. Mr. Suma said
                    that the report received by the Embassy indicated that, even prior to the making
                    by Mr. Dooman of representations, the Japanese Foreign Office had <pb
                        facs="0757" n="661" xml:id="pg_661"/> gotten in touch with the Japanese Navy
                    Department in regard to the bombings.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>M[<hi rend="smallcaps">axwell</hi>] M. H[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >amilton</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
